---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Home Gym Planning Guide - Complete Equipment Checklist">
  <div class="bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto py-16 px-4 sm:py-24 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-900 sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl">
          <span class="block">Complete Home Gym Planning Guide</span>
          <span class="block text-primary-600">and Equipment Checklist</span>
        </h1>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12">
        <div class="relative w-full h-[400px] rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1540497077202-7c8a3999166f?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1200&h=800&q=80" alt="Home Gym Cover Image" class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover">
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Table of Contents -->
      <div class="mt-16 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Table of Contents</h2>
        <nav class="space-y-3">
          <a href="#introduction" class="block text-gray-600 hover:text-primary-600">1. Introduction to Home Gyms</a>
          <a href="#benefits" class="block text-gray-600 hover:text-primary-600">2. Benefits of Having a Home Gym</a>
          <a href="#planning" class="block text-gray-600 hover:text-primary-600">3. Planning Your Home Gym</a>
          <a href="#essential-equipment" class="block text-gray-600 hover:text-primary-600">4. Essential Equipment for a Home Gym</a>
          <a href="#optional-equipment" class="block text-gray-600 hover:text-primary-600">5. Optional Equipment for a Home Gym</a>
          <a href="#setup" class="block text-gray-600 hover:text-primary-600">6. Setting Up Your Home Gym</a>
          <a href="#workout-routine" class="block text-gray-600 hover:text-primary-600">7. Creating a Workout Routine</a>
          <a href="#conclusion" class="block text-gray-600 hover:text-primary-600">8. Conclusion</a>
        </nav>
      </div>

      <!-- Introduction Section -->
      <div id="introduction" class="mt-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Introduction to Home Gyms</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
          Having a home gym can be a great way to stay fit and healthy, without the need for an expensive gym membership. With a home gym, you can work out in the comfort of your own home, at any time of day or night, without having to worry about commuting to a gym or waiting for equipment to become available. A home gym can be a great investment for your health and fitness, as it allows you to work out consistently and make progress towards your goals.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Benefits Section -->
      <div id="benefits" class="mt-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Benefits of Having a Home Gym</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
          There are many benefits to having a home gym, including convenience, cost-effectiveness, and increased motivation. With a home gym, you can work out at any time, without having to worry about gym hours or commuting time. You can also save money on gym memberships and equipment rental fees. A home gym can be a great way to save money on gym memberships and equipment rental fees, as you can purchase equipment upfront and use it for years to come.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Planning Section -->
      <div id="planning" class="mt-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Planning Your Home Gym</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
          When planning your home gym, there are several factors to consider, including space, budget, and equipment needs. You should consider the size of your available space, as well as your budget for equipment and other expenses. You should also think about the types of exercises you want to do, and the equipment you will need to do them. Planning your home gym is an important step in creating a functional and effective workout space.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1517836357463-d25dfeac3438?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&h=600&q=80" alt="Home Gym Equipment Image" class="rounded-xl w-full">
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Essential Equipment Section -->
      <div id="essential-equipment" class="mt-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Essential Equipment for a Home Gym</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
          There are several pieces of equipment that are essential for a home gym, including free weights, a weight bench, a pull-up bar, a treadmill or other cardio equipment, and a set of resistance bands. These pieces of equipment will provide a solid foundation for your home gym, and allow you to perform a variety of exercises.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Optional Equipment Section -->
      <div id="optional-equipment" class="mt-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Optional Equipment for a Home Gym</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
          There are many other pieces of equipment that you can add to your home gym, depending on your specific needs and goals. Some examples include a leg press machine, a chest press machine, a set of kettlebells, a jump rope, and a set of exercise balls. These pieces of equipment can help you to vary your workout routine and target specific muscle groups.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Setup Section -->
      <div id="setup" class="mt-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Setting Up Your Home Gym</h2>
        <div class="md:flex md:space-x-8">
          <div class="md:w-1/2">
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
              Once you have planned and purchased your equipment, it's time to set up your home gym. This involves arranging your equipment in a safe and functional way, as well as adding any decorative elements you like. Setting up your home gym is an important step in creating a space that you will enjoy using.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="md:w-1/2 mt-6 md:mt-0">
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1571902943202-507ec2618e8f?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&h=600&q=80" alt="Home Gym Setup Image" class="rounded-xl w-full">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Workout Routine Section -->
      <div id="workout-routine" class="mt-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Creating a Workout Routine</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
          Once your home gym is set up, it's time to create a workout routine. This involves choosing the exercises you want to do, and creating a schedule for your workouts. A well-planned routine will help you make the most of your home gym and achieve your fitness goals effectively.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Conclusion Section -->
      <div id="conclusion" class="mt-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Conclusion</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
          Creating a home gym is a significant investment in your health and fitness journey. With proper planning, the right equipment, and a dedicated space, you can create an effective workout environment that helps you achieve your fitness goals from the comfort of your home.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA Section -->
      <div class="mt-20">
        <div class="bg-primary-700 rounded-lg shadow-xl overflow-hidden">
          <div class="px-8 py-12 relative">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-white mb-4">Ready to Start Your Home Gym Journey?</h2>
            <p class="text-lg text-primary-100 mb-8">
              Get our complete equipment checklist and start building your perfect home gym today.
            </p>
            <a href="/equipment-guide" class="inline-block px-8 py-4 bg-white text-primary-700 font-bold rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-50 transition-colors">
              View Equipment Guide
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
